quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  32,12,"If only you could see when the guilty ones will bend their heads low before their Lord saying, “Our Lord, We have seen and we have heard. So send us back to the world. We will work righteousness, because we do indeed believe.”"
  32,13,"If We had so willed, We could certainly have brought every soul its true guidance, but this word from Me will come true, “I will fill hell with jinn and humans all together.”"
  32,14,"“So taste this, because you forgot the meeting of this day of yours, indeed We will forget you. Taste the eternal penalty for your harmful deeds.”"
  32,15,"Only those believe in Our signs who when they are recited to them, fall down in adoration, and glorify their Lord by praising Him, and are not puffed up with pride"
  32,16,"Their limbs forsake their beds of sleep, while they call on their Lord in fear and hope, and they give out of the sustenance which We have given them"
  32,17,And no soul knows what pleasure of the eye is kept hidden in reserve for them as a reward for their deeds
  32,18,"Is then the person who believes no better than the person who is rebellious? No, they are not equal"
  32,19,"For those who believe and do righteous deeds, they have gardens as hospitable homes, for those deeds"
  32,20,"As for those who are rebellious, their abode will be the fire. Every time they wish to get away from it, they will be forced deeper into it, and it will be said to them, “Taste the penalty of the fire that you used to deny.”"